name: ax-pre-sup
params: setvar s0, setvar s1, setvar s2, class c0
body: |- wi(w3a(wss(c0, cr), wne(c0, emptycls), wrex(s0, cr, wral(s1, c0, wbr(cv(s1), cltrr, cv(s0))))), wrex(s0, cr, wa(wral(s1, c0, wn(wbr(cv(s0), cltrr, cv(s1)))), wral(s1, cr, wi(wbr(cv(s1), cltrr, cv(s0)), wrex(s2, c0, wbr(cv(s1), cltrr, cv(s2))))))))
comment: A nonempty, bounded-above set of reals has a supremum. Axiom 22 of 22 for real and complex numbers, justified by theorem ~ axpre-sup . Note: Normally new proofs would use ~ axsup . (New usage is discouraged.) (Contributed by NM, 13-Oct-2005.)
